<br>
I used to be a mage, now I play the shaman in our group.  I quit my mage a long time ago because I felt weak and 'cheated' after kunark for a chanter and didn't regret it at all.  Now as a shaman and seperated by time I wonder if I was wrong.  (or things have changed ALOT)<br>
<br>
The mage is the anchor of our group, he has a burnt staff and focus items.  Even without clarity his damage output is amazing (he does usually have a PotG though).  I use a JBB but the mage, wow.  He pulls 2 or 3 at a time and use his pet solo on one while we kill off the other one or two mobs.  No down time at all, the necro has to feed me mana even with canabilize and a fungi tunic so I can keep up the buffs.  I am not slowing at all except the higher level named spawns.<br>
<br>
Anyway, we are about to ding 49th and expect a big increase in power in addition to the new beastlord mana regen spell.  Do you think we would be better off with the beastlord or my old mage, now 55th, say when we all ding 51 or so?<br>
<br>
Also looking for hunting advice, will post in the proper forum for that though.<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/useek9.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Seek 9</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master Summoner</span><br>  Posts: 589<br> <font color=#333333>(9/4/02 9:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=686.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: An all pet four way is a blast.</span><hr size=1> This is a mage board.   People here are generally pro-Mage and will suggest you play your Mage if that is what you want to do <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<br>
In all seriousness, your group already has a Mage, a Mage who is on the verge of level 49 greatness.    At that level, he will no doubt far eclipse the damage output of the other folks in your group.   But this power will level off a great deal as he gets into his mid 50's (as I am seeing for myself).  Of course, he will gain lots of utility to offset that...anyway...if you keep the Shaman, you bring a vast amount of utility to the team that they will lose.<br>
<br>
But, adding another Mage will without doubt increase your overall damage potential quite a bit.  Mages stack pretty well, and having 2 Mages pets and a Necro pet...that is a big shield for mobs to break before they get to the weak caster bodies.<br>
<br>
Naturally, I am pro Mage, and if I were you, I would be going back to my Mage in this group.    But, if you are interested in more versatility, your group will benefit more from having the Shaman there.<br>
<br>
